<statement>
<image width="33%"  pi:generated="problems/images/489e4622256ff1d52426da688cc605d3.png" /><p>
Suppose a = 10 and A = 25 degrees. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
c = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place.  Give angles in <em>degrees</em>
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>21.4</li><li>23.7</li><li>65.0</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p>For the length of the other leg,</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\tan{{\left({25}\right)}}}=\frac{{10}}{{b}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}=\frac{{10}}{{\tan{{\left({25}\right)}}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}\approx{21.445069205096}\approx{21.4}</m>.</p>
<p>For the third side</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={10}^{{2}}+{21.445069205096}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={100}+{459.89099321134}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={559.89099321134}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{559.89099321134}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{23.662015831525}\approx{23.7}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{25}^{\circ}\approx{65}^{\circ}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

